<Author>ddoran
<Content>DR VETERAN OPINION Background: I have been coming to the DR yearly since being a Peace Corps vol. here many years ago, I just love the Domincan people (and their beer, baseball and beautiful women).The hotel sends their representative to wait for you at the bottom of plane's stairs (they own the airport as well). They then drive you a quick 15 minutes to the hotel where you are checked-in right inside your own room. The beach is all of 15 yards away so you can be relaxing less than 1 hour after arriving. TBH is located inside the Punat Cana ResortThis is not an AI hotel. Our breakfasts were included (as well as 2 dinners). We would eat lunch at the main pool at the Punta Cana resort and we had dinner twice at the Bamboo (one was Domincan food/dance night) and twice as La Yola where you sit outside and view the sea from this Marina spot . We could have eaten there every night.We journeyed by hotel car to nearby Cap Cana three times while there to see the competitive resort and to eat at the new (but no customers) higher end restaurants. Mitre was well worth the trip as well as the Bistro Marrana. We did not go to the just opened Aqua Mar but looked good and we ate at Amarcord and dont bother to eat there. As this area is still being built, it is realy a ghost town for nowActivities: we did the beach buggy along the ocean and we do this every year and try and get muddier ever time: goes along the beach at nearby Cabo Engano. Deep sea fishing: lets just say that we had rough seas and leave it at that and my wife made me promise to never do that to here again! Golf: rented clubs and played at 7.15 (course open at 7.30 but they let me go out alone with a cart and caddy). Pebble Beach style played the 18 holes in exactly 2 hours as there was no one ahead of us. I wasnt going to play but very glad I did.Spa: Had a 90 minute message in our package. Very nice and you can pay extra and they will do this in the beach area.Walk: unlike Bavaro beach, you can walk to the left for 25 minutes and there is nothing at all until you reach the spa. Tranquill! Sunset Horse back: the horses were older than we were. This was just ok and it is every Thursday 5 to 6.Used the golf cart to get around and rode the bikes some as well. To get to La Yola, you will need the cart and ask direction to to the Marina.The staff was always great. They even called the restaurant La Yola ahead of our reservation to make sure my beer was super cold as they put in in a freezer to get it 'bien fria.The question to answer is would we come back. Our reply is that we told them we would be back next time but for 2 weeks!This is a tranquill place and it is best to come if that is your interest. No discos etcI read the reviews on TBH last year at tripadvisor and there was a tip on bidding for a room here at a luxury discount spot. Go to www.luxurylink.com. We did this and it worked great and saved some money. We are going to Peru to see our peace Corps daughter and will use luxury link to book high end places there as well.If anyone has any questions, just email me.DD 
